          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary>Do I need PA PUC authority if I'm crossing state lines?</summary>
            <p>No. If you're hauling interstate (origin or destination outside PA), you only need federal FMCSA authority (USDOT + MC number). PA PUC is only for intrastate - both pickup and delivery within Pennsylvania. Most truckers only need federal authority.</p>
          </details>
          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary>How much does Pennsylvania trucking insurance cost?</summary>
            <p>For new authorities, expect $12,000-$18,000/year for a single truck with $750K liability. PA rates reflect the high-traffic corridors and urban density around Philadelphia and the Lehigh Valley. Get a quote to see your actual numbers.</p>
          </details>
          <details class="faq-item">
